(210, '2015-08-12 10:32:00', NULL, 1, 130, 'Touching the Void', 'touching_the_void', 1, 'In the mid-80&#39;s two young climbers attempted to reach the summit of Siula Grande in Peru; a feat that had previously been attempted but never achieved. With an extra man looking after base camp&#44; Simon and Joe set off to scale the mount in one long push over several days. The peak is reached&#44; however on the descent Joe falls and breaks his leg. Despite what it means&#44; the two continue with Simon letting Joe out on a rope for 300 meters&#44; then descending to join him and so on. However when Joe goes out over an overhang with no way of climbing back up&#44; Simon makes the decision to cut the rope. Joe falls into a crevasse and Simon&#44; assuming him dead&#44; continues back down. Joe however survives the fall and was lucky to hit a ledge in the crevasse. This is the story of how he got back down.                ', '<p>In the mid-80&#39;s two young climbers attempted to reach the summit of Siula Grande in Peru; a feat that had previously been attempted but never achieved. With an extra man looking after base camp&#44; Simon and Joe set off to scale the mount in one long push over several days. The peak is reached&#44; however on the descent Joe falls and breaks his leg. Despite what it means&#44; the two continue with Simon letting Joe out on a rope for 300 meters&#44; then descending to join him and so on. However when Joe goes out over an overhang with no way of climbing back up&#44; Simon makes the decision to cut the rope. Joe falls into a crevasse and Simon&#44; assuming him dead&#44; continues back down. Joe however survives the fall and was lucky to hit a ledge in the crevasse. This is the story of how he got back down.                </p>\n', 'daa1e7b469b4e1945772f68a1efb4b39', 1, 1439368320, 0, 'always', 'live', 'markdown', '', '0379557', '11194', 'https://image.tmdb.org/t/p/original/ozExRDtiwDqyIcRfZ7Zi14EPbiX.jpg', 'Documentary&#44; Adventure&#44; Drama