(479, '2015-08-12 11:50:00', NULL, 1, 399, 'Lincoln', 'lincoln', 1, 'In 1865&#44; as the American Civil War winds inexorably toward conclusion&#44; U.S. president Abraham Lincoln endeavors to achieve passage of the landmark constitutional amendment which will forever ban slavery from the United States. However&#44; his task is a race against time&#44; for peace may come at any time&#44; and if it comes before the amendment is passed&#44; the returning southern states will stop it before it can become law. Lincoln must&#44; by almost any means possible&#44; obtain enough votes from a recalcitrant Congress before peace arrives and it is too late. Yet the president is torn&#44; as an early peace would save thousands of lives. As the nation confronts its conscience over the freedom of its entire population&#44; Lincoln faces his own crisis of conscience -- end slavery or end the war.                ', '<p>In 1865&#44; as the American Civil War winds inexorably toward conclusion&#44; U.S. president Abraham Lincoln endeavors to achieve passage of the landmark constitutional amendment which will forever ban slavery from the United States. However&#44; his task is a race against time&#44; for peace may come at any time&#44; and if it comes before the amendment is passed&#44; the returning southern states will stop it before it can become law. Lincoln must&#44; by almost any means possible&#44; obtain enough votes from a recalcitrant Congress before peace arrives and it is too late. Yet the president is torn&#44; as an early peace would save thousands of lives. As the nation confronts its conscience over the freedom of its entire population&#44; Lincoln faces his own crisis of conscience -- end slavery or end the war.                </p>\n', '081d9ee9e2baaf685c5f09939e58ac95', 1, 1439373000, 0, 'always', 'live', 'markdown', '', '0443272', '72976', 'https://image.tmdb.org/t/p/original/gkkiDu9srCCbCMxGKwNwKCxK7KF.jpg', 'Biography&#44; Drama&#44; History&#44; War', 'Steven Spie